# Scoped refactor prompt (docs mirror)

**Canonical file:** [`.cursor/rules/cursor-scoped-refactor-prompt.mdc`](../.cursor/rules/cursor-scoped-refactor-prompt.mdc)

**Greenfield development** from `ARCHITECTURE.md`: [`.cursor/rules/cursor-scoped-development-prompt.mdc`](../.cursor/rules/cursor-scoped-development-prompt.mdc)

That rule **auto-loads** when editing `lib/features/**`, `app/(main)/**`, `components2/metadata/**`, and related paths. For large refactors, explicitly `@`-mention it and paste `TARGET_SCOPE`.

## Paste in Cursor

```txt
@.cursor/rules/cursor-scoped-refactor-prompt.mdc

TARGET_SCOPE:
lib/features/<module>/<area>/**
app/(main)/[locale]/o/[orgSlug]/apps/<module>/<segment>/**
tests/unit/<matching>*.test.ts

REFACTOR_KIND: full-stack
MODULE: <module>
PRESERVE_UI: yes
```

Full verdict text, skills stack, residue cleanup, verification gates, and report template are in the Cursor rule — not duplicated here.
